    <header>
        <h1><marquee behavior="alternate" ;bgcolor="maroon" ;height="1000">Nihari</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>3 lbs beef shank, cut into pieces</li>
            <li>2 large onions, thinly sliced</li>
            <li>4 tablespoons wheat flour</li>
            <li>1/4 cup ginger-garlic paste</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon ghee</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons Nihari masala powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon red chili powder</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon cumin powder</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon coriander powder</li>
            <li>4 cups water</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>Fresh ginger slices for garnish</li>
            <li>Fresh coriander leaves for garnish</li>
            <li>Sliced green chilies for garnish</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>seafood</li>
            <li>nonveg</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a large pot, heat ghee and sauté sliced onions until golden brown.</li>
            <li>Add ginger-garlic paste and cook until the raw smell disappears.</li>
            <li>Add wheat flour and continue to sauté until it turns golden brown.</li>
            <li>Add beef shank pieces and sear until browned on all sides.</li>
            <li>Add Nihari masala powder, turmeric powder, red chili powder, cumin powder, and coriander powder. Mix well.</li>
            <li>Pour in water and bring the mixture to a boil. Reduce heat, cover, and simmer until the meat is tender.</li>
            <li>Adjust salt to taste.</li>
            <li>Garnish with fresh ginger slices, coriander leaves, and sliced green chilies.</li>
            <li>Serve hot with naan or steamed rice.</li>
            <li>Enjoy the rich and flavorful Nihari!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
